n gate(they can‚Äôt bring you past this as the golf cart has no plate so it‚Äôs about half way down) but we used to love the walk as very close to benitses village so we used to stroll down to there too, has a path the whole way bit of a work out walking back up the hill but again once you reach the main gate the golf cart will pick you up and bring you back and no harm as all the over indulging of food!!üòù Room was lovely and clean, serviced twice a day, has a mini fridge(handy to store water, they provide plenty of bottled water also) The hotel was spotless throughout. They also can organize a taxi for you ‚Ç¨40 to old town, we also went to Mesonghi one evening and the taxi was ‚Ç¨35 to here, if you hire a car the staff will park it and bring it to you when required. Would deffo stay here again and recommend it to a friend. Thanks for a fab trip, enjoy your break for the off season well deserved to all the staff.ü•∞","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"Victoria","rating":5,"text":"I stayed at this hotel for the second time and it was just as fabulous as I remembered. The staff are so professional and friendly. Thank you to the lovely guy who drove us to and from the beach every day üòä. The room was beautiful (the view!) and really comfortable.\n\nThe food was also amazing. We had an incredible three-course dinner at Sofrito which included king prawns and ceviche, and even the beach restaurant was fantastic - the grilled octopus tacos were out of this world.\n\nI also had a wonderful massage; both the masseuse and the spa receptionist were so kind and made me feel completely relaxed.\n\nI can‚Äôt wait to come back!","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"Open Kloset By Karina","rating":5,"text":"Dive into Corfu‚Äôs Eclectic Spirit üåøüåäüá¨üá∑\nwe spent an unforgettable day at this resort,  enjoying a serene spa escape and a delicious lunch with breathtaking Ionian Sea views.\n\nPerched on a lush hill above the turquoise waters, this 5‚≠êÔ∏è resort ‚Äî the first banyantreehotels property in Europe ‚Äî perfectly blends authentic Greek hospitality with Asian-inspired serenity.\n\nFrom elegant suites and private villas to the world-class wellness center and seafront dining, every detail captures the soul of Corfu. And that infinity pool? Crowned Best Hotel Pool in the World (Prix Villegiature 2022) ‚Äî pure perfection. üíô‚ú®\n100% recommend this place!","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Brid Nunn","rating":5,"text":"What a wonderful stay at the Angsana resort. We were here for my husband‚Äôs birthday and got a lovely surprise on the actual day of a lovely birthday cake, Prosecco and even a candle! We have been here for 9 nights and the hotel is beyond amazing ‚Ä¶‚Ä¶ from the upgraded suite we were given ‚Ä¶.. to the incredible view ‚Ä¶.. to the excellent service and politeness of every single member of staff. Breakfast is something to behold ‚Ä¶.. a stunning display of food to cater for all tastes ‚Ä¶.. we had a couple of rainy days and were able to take advantage of the aqua aerobics and the gym and indoor pool. The young gentlemen who got our car for us when we wanted to go out ‚Ä¶‚Ä¶ the pretty beach ‚Ä¶.. the housekeeping staff who were fantastic and always ensure we had coffee pods and water ‚Ä¶‚Ä¶.. and the steak in the restaurant - best we have ever had!! A wonderful experience and totally deserving of 10/10 ‚Ä¶. Many thanks.","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"lpz","rating":5,"text":"What an amazing experience! We had the pleasure of staying here last week and were absolutely stunned by everything this resort had to offer. The resort‚Äôs infrastructure is superb; the way the infinity pool seems to flow seamlessly into the deep blue far-stretching Ionian Sea is simply breathtaking. The staff were exceptional as well: always smiling, welcoming, and ready to assist with anything we needed. The on-site dining options were also fantastic. Our dinner at Oribu was a highlight, especially the dessert, which felt worthy of a Michelin star. Thank you for a truly wonderful experience!","time":"3 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
