 I travel all over the world due to professional obligations and we always try to stay to the best hotels. This is an amazing hotel! You should definitely stay there. The atmosphere, the food, the staff, the live music, the rooms are all perfect! Highly Highly recommended! I hope we could stay more but we had to go back to NY.","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Cleopatra Aitken","rating":5,"text":"A truly special place!\n\nWe thoroughly enjoyed our stay at Kinsterna Hotel ‚Äî it‚Äôs a truly special place where you can feel the love and detail poured into every corner. From the beautifully restored architecture to the lush grounds, everything has been so thoughtfully curated.\n\nBreakfast was incredible, and both the taverna and main restaurant served some of the best food we had in Greece ‚Äî absolutely 10/10. The pool area is stunning, and the whole experience felt luxurious yet grounded in nature and history.\n\nThe only small suggestion we‚Äôd make is around guest orientation. The property is large and full of interesting areas and activities, but we weren‚Äôt given a proper briefing on arrival. The person who took us to reception offered little detail. We ended up missing some of the lovely complimentary activities like the bread making and honey collecting, which mostly happen on weekends but managed to do a garden tour with the agronomist which was special.\n\nA simple welcome tour or clearer communication would make a big difference.\n\nThat aside, our stay was exceptional ‚Äî peaceful, delicious, and full of charm. We‚Äôd return in a heartbeat!","time":"6 months ago"},{"author":"Panagiotis Farmakis","rating":5,"text":"A truly exceptional stay! The hotel offers top-notch accommodation with outstanding service from the staff. Rich in Byzantine charm, it beautifully blends tradition with comfort in the heart of Greek nature near Monemvasia castle. The traditional Greek food is absolutely delicious, and the pool area is perfect for relaxing. Highly recommended for an authentic and peaceful getaway!","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"Polina Chimonidou","rating":5,"text":"We had a wonderful stay at Kinsterna Hotel with our 9-month-old baby ‚Äì they truly made us feel at home. The hotel offers a true five-star experience while preserving its traditional character and charm. Visitors should take some time to learn about the rich history of the estate and the surrounding area ‚Äì it‚Äôs truly fascinating. The staff were incredibly polite and helpful, and the owner is hands-on, which really shows in every detail. Kisses from Cyprus ‚Äì see you again soon!","time":"5 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
