each Resort in Porto Heli, and the experience was truly luxurious. The service is top notch professional, attentive, and always with a smile. The food is excellent, both in quality and presentation, with a variety of delicious options that made every meal memorable. The gym is well equipped and more than sufficient for a holiday workout.\n\nHowever, it‚Äôs important to note that the overall atmosphere of the hotel is very quiet and, at times, a bit too calm. Aside from the beautiful pool area, there isn‚Äôt much else to do on site. The beach is nice to look at but not particularly inviting for swimming or spending the day.\n\nThis resort is ideal for couples looking for a peaceful, romantic escape in a high-end setting. It‚Äôs not the best choice for families with kids or travelers looking for entertainment and a lively environment. That said, if you‚Äôre after tranquility and elegance, Nikki Beach Porto Heli delivers exactly that.","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"Captain Denny Diary","rating":1,"text":"We booked Nikki Beach Porto Cheli expecting the brand‚Äôs promised quality and standards, but our experience was extremely disappointing.\n\n1.\tThe rooftop balcony furniture and jacuzzi were not just worn ‚Äî they were clearly old, damaged, and unacceptable for a hotel in this price range.\n\n2.\tThe jacuzzi was dirty on our arrival even after we specifically requested before arrived an extra cleaning. This shows a serious lack of attention to hygiene.\n\n3.\tThe room was totally misrepresented. There was no real sea view, except from the balcony, and the interior layout looked nothing like the booking site photos. This is misleading advertising, misrepresenting and unacceptable.\n\n4.\tThe reception staff was painfully slow and indifferent. It was also obvious that since the hotel was about to close for the season, service had dropped to a bare minimum, even the bar didnot have fresh fruits to serve. Only the parking team and the breakfast staff seemed to make an effort ‚Äî everything else was far below standard.\n\nFor the amount we paid ( almost 953‚Ç¨ for 2 nights )the service and quality were absolutely not worth it. The photos online are misleading / misrepresenting the room and the actual room quality and arrangements did not match at all. Sadly, this property has nothing in common with the Nikki Beach brand‚Äôs promised standards. A very disappointing stay....","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"◊®◊ï◊¢◊ô ◊ó◊®◊ï◊ë◊ô","rating":5,"text":"We had an absolutely amazing stay at Nikki Beach Hotel!\nThe staff all around the hotel ‚Äî from the pool team to the breakfast crew and everyone in between ‚Äî were so friendly and welcoming.\nThe food was outstanding, and the pool was perfect, with great music and a fantastic DJ creating the perfect atmosphere.\nThank you for giving us truly unforgettable days!","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"J AH","rating":5,"text":"My recent stay at this hotel was nothing short of perfection. From the moment we arrived, we were treated to the highest standards of hospitality, and it truly felt like a five-star experience in every way.\n\nThe room was absolutely fantastic,spacious, immaculately clean, and incredibly comfortable. The bed was like a cloud, ensuring a perfect night''s sleep after long days in the sun. It was a true haven of relaxation.\n\nNow, let''s talk about the food... it was exquisite! The breakfast buffet had an incredible variety of fresh and delicious options. We enjoyed delicious meals at the hotel''s restaurants for dinner, but the absolute highlight was the food served at the beach bar. The fresh seafood and casual dishes were so delicious we found ourselves having lunch there every single day. Even the room service menu was top-tier; we ordered in one evening and were blown away by the quality and flavor.\n\nWhat truly elevated our stay from excellent to extraordinary was the staff. A special mention must be made of Katerina Aggelopoulou. She was an absolute gem always attentive, incredibly helpful with any request we had, and her warm, smiling presence brightened our every day. She is a tremendous asset to your team and embodies the spirit of genuine hospitality.\nThe entire staff was smiley , helpful and welcoming .\nWe cannot recommend this hotel highly enough and are already dreaming of our next visit. Thank you for a memorable and flawless holiday Nikki Beach beach resort and spa Porto heli .","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Hamza Debbarh","rating":4,"text":"Very nice hotel with fantastic view on the marina and generous size of the room with large bathroom and more than enough space for a family of three or even four and a fantastic view from the terrace / balcony on Porto Heli Marina. Good buffet for a boutique hotel, the dinner at the dolce vita was very good as well with a fantastic sunset view. The beach unfortunately is not clean (too much seaweed‚Ä¶), doesn‚Äôt seem to be  swimmable but the pool is nice and has great views on the marina. Overall, I would say one of the best spots in Porto Heli to discover and explore the area with fantastic experiences of yachting and swimming in very unexpected and beautiful places. We definitely recommend.","time":"4 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
