getting married at Ktima on 14.10.25\nI can honestly say it was the best day of both our lives. Everybody that works at Ktima are friendly & went above & beyond to make ours & our guests experience unforgettable!\nThe food is exceptional, the views are breathtaking.\nI would especially like to thank both Nicole our wedding planner & Manolis the owner of Ktima for all their assistance in making our dream wedding come true ‚ù§Ô∏è","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"Viktor Miljesic","rating":1,"text":"I rarely write negative reviews, but my experience at Ktima Lindos was disappointing enough that I feel it‚Äôs worth sharing. We ordered steaks medium, and they came out completely overcooked‚Äînot once, but twice. Despite giving them a second chance, the kitchen still couldn‚Äôt get it right. To make things worse, no refund or compensation was offered, just a shrug.\n\nThe only redeeming factor here is the view, which is admittedly beautiful‚Äîbut if you actually care about good food and service, stay away. Lindos has plenty of other restaurants that deliver both.","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Georgina Tseroni","rating":5,"text":"I had such a wonderful experience here! The cocktails were amazing, but the food was even more impressive. The view is truly remarkable, the kind you just don‚Äôt forget, and the team working there were so kind and helpful, making the whole evening even better. This place is definitely a must-stop when in Rhodes, and I‚Äôd absolutely go back again. Highly recommend!","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Rob Parfitt","rating":5,"text":"An unforgettable experience at Ktima, Lindos.\n\nFrom start to finish, dining at Ktima was an absolute highlight of our trip. The setting is truly one of the most beautiful places I‚Äôve ever had a meal, with breathtaking views paired with a serene atmosphere that makes the whole experience feel special.\n\nThe service was exceptional across the board. Every member of staff struck the perfect balance, attentive without ever being pushy or interruptive. What seemed to be the head lady was simply amazing: warm, professional, and clearly passionate about making guests feel welcome. Toward the end of our meal, another member of the team, possibly a manager, came over to take payment. Rather than just processing the bill and moving on, he took the time to ask where we were from, where we were staying, and even offered thoughtful recommendations for other restaurants to try. It was a genuinely refreshing interaction that showed they care more about your experience than just your custom.\n\nThe food was phenomenal. The seafood linguine, in particular, deserves a special mention. It was hands down the best bowl of pasta I‚Äôve ever eaten. Every bite was packed with flavour, and it was cooked to perfection. The cocktails were also excellent, beautifully made and perfectly balanced.\n\nOn top of everything, the service was fast and efficient without feeling rushed. Ktima gets everything right, from location and ambiance to food and hospitality. If you‚Äôre in Lindos, do not miss this place.","time":"6 months ago"},{"author":"Billy Gray","rating":5,"text":"We''ve been to this place a few times now and it never disappoints. The food is always amazing, the drinks are spot on, and the views are unreal. The staff are super attentive and friendly ‚Äî you really feel looked after. You can tell they really care about the place and their guests. Already looking forward to going back again!","time":"3 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
