 Not too many children around the pool so we could do our daily swim easily and the gym had enough machines and fitness equipment to do a good work-out. The newer big size pool is perfect for swimming laps and 1.40 meter deep.\n\nWeekly there are different events, our favorite is the Greek evening with traditional Cretan dishes and dancing. In the setting with the church it feels you are in a small local village square.\n\nWe stayed many times in the suite with private pool, the suite is spacious and very private. The pool is big enough to refresh and swim a bit or drink a wine along it. We like the showers and bath amenities and slept really well.\n\nThere are not many places in Crete with a complete product like the St. Nicolas Bay hotel with private beach, parking and different restaurant facilities. Mostly we eat in the different restaurants and did not take the half board plan but this is also possible. We like also to visit the town of Agios Nikolaos for the other nights, easy acces and taxi for 8 euro.\n\nWe will definitely be back!! Thank you for al the great moments so far.\n\nSome tips to visit: Voulisma Beach and the beach club there to have lunch, The town of Agios Nikolaos day time or evening and Ammoudi Beach.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Keith Vartanian (Keith Vartanian)","rating":5,"text":"We were here for the tail end of our honeymoon, and when I say this was the best stay that myself or my wife have ever had, I mean it.\n\nFrom the moment we got there we were treated like family - everyone knew our names, greeted us with joy and went above and beyond to ask us if we need anything.\n\nMy wife has a gluten allergy, and from day one, whether it was breakfast, lunch, or dinner, they knew to bring over gluten free bread for her, and had the chef come out and talk to her about what she could and could not have.\n\nFor our final night, they offered to move us to an upgraded room as an extension of warmth for our honeymoon - unfortunately we had to decline as it meant packing up early on a day we had an excursion planned. So, instead, they surprised us with a dinner on the house at their finest restaurant, and gave us the best seat in the house to look out at the sunset over the bay. This included a full meal, as well as a bottle of champagne. Everyone on staff was warm and asked us about our wedding, gave us personal stories, etc.\n\nAll this to say this place has the service of a 5 star stay, and the personality of a local bed and breakfast. Well-done to all involved, we never like to return to hotels but we both have agreed that we plan on coming back here as often as we can afford üòÇ","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"NIKOS-REVAZ NEBADZE","rating":5,"text":"Excellent 5-star hotel! Everything was perfect ‚Äî stunning sea view from the room, high-quality service, and great comfort. The cuisine was varied and delicious, and the staff was always professional, friendly, and helpful. A truly wonderful stay ‚Äî we will definitely return!","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Morgan Giddings","rating":5,"text":"We stayed here for 7 nights in June for our babymoon. It was absolutely perfect. The team went above and beyond to make it a special trip. The room was pristine, well appointed, and the room pool cleaned daily. The breakfast had so many good options and from European choices to Greek specialties. We walked to town each day or night, there is a sidewalk most of the time and we didn‚Äôt feel unsafe in any way (other reviews said it was dangerous with cars etc). The staff was kind and welcoming. The manager Alexandros is an absolute gem and the lodging is a reflection of his caring and hard work. We‚Äôll be back!","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"Emily Heitmann","rating":5,"text":"This resort is absolutely magical! The views! The pools! The stellar service! We stayed in the Grand Animos Villa and it was absolutely perfect. The pool is massive and the privacy and unobstructed views meant that we rarely left the backyard. Plus, we had a private cove that offered direct access into the ocean. Fish were everywhere! The team was so helpful in planning catamaran trips as well as local excursions. And the resort food was so delicious. We are already missing that breakfast buffet! We cannot wait to return!","time":"5 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
