tributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/104669275548637096110\">Can Riera De La Pineda</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN18Jzr5jF5bNIKBzsOv0U1m6TwgEo1LNQoy9iYDwjTtLSq_A5GyROqQjngO8mKevH_vKk9Hi-hxjYR0j_ctIhmcP2OIPqSO93QImabteODwx714OPd2nB3ro8bpigYZ8YngyDVK2MJSHii3bcUF-xJr3Y0cwrcLyVImaP8Tq3LF7OU8NiYX3P6sDnxOKFQzLNe5eSvF77ZAQ2zHXBqLjlXlw0wn4-Bx2Z3gpiOhmoOhEbAqRNgPnv4bssttmntDi5OvXf4Dnco4SuaeKIWogobmloqIwIxKA_SoUL6W2WJr3dWXFIC8lkQ32GjV_6KQCW_OBSQPGu0j44sh684NAGvwSzJPRLRTjP_3ShEQ9shCs4C87cWIPB-1Ic7HQKzDD9a8rWSwKRbRM6_Tgt88w-vWEDMQAodA0RRaew78LQJwNA","width":3024,"height":4032,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/111260239309761177600\">Alice Bragg</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN365Q4YOwM1SHqKYzPocXSOkjMPsaC3gMDdD4G2coWol3eIyK8_pz7rJb8wt5hZ7LEWZNH_zG7b_ylsaRp70K4Vm4czE-cejZaAbQM9hrz2ixLwVxStYzMCWH-hiOULVYhMqu46m9SH4CoKrjm2xJD4Ti6V2vyP2it2XIjs94_eoH0Ae4DX3gaSOkKlGXFF4O7O97eqx8E55_jJ_DGCdNQ7IyHEeLjb-xEqZSZfRBA_vCYY3wBbgHzH-aE90mhafp448eKT9KfjhmPfKGQpq1I_ouumiZI5xDi_pcABIdt_4g","width":450,"height":450,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/104669275548637096110\">Can Riera De La Pineda</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Larne O''Donoghue","rating":5,"text":"There are moments in life that exist outside of time. The world stops, and all that remains are the people who matter most in one of the most beautiful places on earth. Our wedding at Can Riera was one of those moments.\n\nCan Riera isn‚Äôt just beautiful, it‚Äôs breathtaking. Nestled alone in the hills, for three days we existed in our own little universe with nature all around us. It was us, the chickens, Marta and acres and acres of stunning mountains. The house has stood for a thousand years and you can feel every bit of that history. We could literally feel the love in the walls.\n\nAnd then there was Marta, our host.\n\nMarta didn‚Äôt just host our wedding, she became family. She held our hands through the chaos of planning, connecting dots we couldn‚Äôt see, answering questions we didn‚Äôt know to ask. Every detail was touched by her care. The local butcher‚Äôs feast at our welcome BBQ. The warm bread that arrived each morning from the village bakery. She made everything so effortless.\n\nOur ceremony was in the forest with a gentle stream as the soundtrack to our vows. The kids were splashing around there all weekend.\n\nWhen we left Can Riera, we cried twice. Once from the overwhelming happiness of what we‚Äôd experienced. And again from the sadness of leaving.\n\nMarta and Can Riera are woven into our story forever. They live in our hearts, in our memories, in the very fabric of our marriage.\n\nThank you, Marta. Thank you, Can Riera. You gave us a weekend that was beyond our wildest dreams.","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Alice Bragg","rating":5,"text":"Had the pleasure of staying here for 3 nights over the weekend of my wedding. The location is beautiful and the house is also magical. The real standout here however is Marta, who runs the venue. She is incredibly helpful and friendly and really helped alleviate a lot of stress and anxiety over the wedding itself and the whole weekend. She was accommodating and communicative and we were really really happy with her! We did have a few issues, namely with the actual house itself which is old, the electrics were patchy with some lights not working in darker areas of the house and no hot water on our final night and morning. There are dogs on site which if you like dogs is a nice treat! However one of these dogs is left chained outside overnight and on our final night she barked throughout the entire night, some guests were unaffected but others did have a sleepless night because of it, there was someone on site overnight so we are not sure why nothing was done but other than this the experience was almost perfect!","time":"7 months ago"},{"author":"Rosalind Warren","rating":5,"text":"Thank you so much to Marta and Pau for the most incredible wedding weekend that exceeded our expectations!\nCan Riera de la Pineda is a little piece of heaven on earth - if you are looking for a wedding venue that is full of love, beauty, and comes with everything you need for a wedding, this is the place for you.\n\nWe booked Can Riera for all our wedding activities and had many of our friends and family staying there with us, which was so special to us as Expats. We organized a rehearsal dinner on Friday, our wedding on Saturday, and an Asado on Sunday - all at Can Riera, and we couldn''t be happier with our choice.\nCan Riera is gorgeous - it is so well maintained, and is a huge property that you can customize to suit your needs. From our ceremony in the forest, our appertivo in the orchard, dinner in the field, and then party by the pool - the huge space lets you have a great flow to your day and keep your guests exploring new areas.\n\nThe property itself is beautiful but what may be even better is Marta and Pau. During the wedding planning process Marta was wonderful to work with - quick to respond, helpful, and I always felt I was in safe hands. She gave great recommendations and helped us immensely. During the wedding weekend Pau was so wonderful with us - he was helping every day to make sure that things went smoothly, and was so supportive and nice to us. We genuinely felt like he was one of our guests because of how nice he was. He let us feel like we were at home and use the space as we needed - he was even supportive of us jumping in the pool at the end of the wedding and greeted us with big towels and a smile!\n\nThank you to Marta, Pau, and everyone at Can Riera. You made our wedding weekend feel like home. We will never forget it.","time":"a year ago"},{"author":"Andr√© De Cara","rating":5,"text":"Marta helped my wife and I plan the entire wedding from beginning to end, she was extremely helpful, accommodating and thoughtful! On top of that Can Riera is as charming as a fairy tale and I couldn‚Äôt have asked for anything to be different. Our special day was even more special with their support and care","time":"7 months ago"},{"author":"Marion Balinoff","rating":5,"text":"This wedding venue was love at first sight. We loved the forest by the little river where we did our ceremony and made use of the beautiful garden for our reception. Marta and her niece have been so helpful and accommodating. We couldn''t have dreamt of a better place to get married. Would recommend it to anyone wanting to get married in the mountain/forest","time":"a year ago"}]'::jsonb,
