s staying both on and off the property and it worked well. Be mindful of the dirt road driving up! I would absolutely recommend Mas Torroella for a wedding!","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"David leach","rating":5,"text":"We stayed there for our daughters wedding. This has to be the most amazing venue I have ever been to. A superb venue looked after by the fabulous Sylvia and her staff. We can''t praise them enough for their help and attention to detail. Yes, the drive up can be challenging but fun! and then you arrive at the spectacular location. thank you.David","time":"6 months ago"},{"author":"D K","rating":5,"text":"If you''re looking for a place to celebrate your wedding in style, Mas Torroella is a truly magical choice.\n\nWhat we loved most was not only the beautiful architecture and peaceful setting, but the fact that you can stay for a few days with your guests and really enjoy the experience. There are plenty of rooms to host your closest friends and family in comfort.","time":"6 months ago"},{"author":"Sean Mayes","rating":5,"text":"We visited for a Wedding and were so impressed by the venue. Everything was done to such a high standard. The buildings and outside were stunning.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Elizabeth Innes","rating":5,"text":"Beautiful wedding. The most beautiful place ever. Like a fairy tale. Picture perfect. It''s beyond 5star. Food was amazing and service was excellent üëç I will never forget this experience üôè btw lemon tree''s and orange tree''s and rosemary growing on the grounds. Absolutely breathtaking scenery","time":"7 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
