NzP0iLOgM08Ba7EqU1hYz9yJdt83w7wEplLQhPW2aTBBtoEPFPR4yiMtkUqXSknyj9jHim3mnooWsD25IU8D51Qy5zM_hKS-FtX8QU7pSAM8DMG77tSAMl0lvu94D6duZO5BdYcG79pFPBNuI6CquTHC8jW-dG2vnbk9-a6P9pB3eLO1uW2ROVsEjVfFJxUw","width":900,"height":600,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/115807646129304394437\">Hotel Cap Rocat</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN0m4EvReo4r4IBYhtD8PBaNpdI_WJNqJppNQilx07N-nOU3S24LQ-i2p1p1Y-KFCYABg5yb68v86GZYHXYvF8AdGoGjSzXY1JMDH78jG-N1eTwZ75XHZLA4gS1a1c_9_fEmgt863kVeNrY2wom9hdvYxUSC-IoRCn20OR5K7IKH1qhxVyJPou_fZLvx6Cu-tqcrA01dej5RBXb02zLN2ER2Z-Dl9uxy7zdqwcv0pZfL40tI9Adx9P17zxxHt66TanAsRLD-EPMh8zEf-XGYmptTb7kVYqVFZladBYihzuuL1w","width":2912,"height":3636,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/115807646129304394437\">Hotel Cap Rocat</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Joseph Ball","rating":5,"text":"This was by far our favorite hotel we‚Äôve ever stayed at. From when I booked it a year ago up until we departed, the attention to detail was near perfect. Every aspect of your stay is done so well I was actually waiting for something to go wrong and it never did. Concierge crafted the perfect itinerary for us and made adjustments onsite as needed. There‚Äôs also such a low amount of hotel guests that it feels like it‚Äôs your own place. The daily breakfast, sea club, and general service from all the hotel employees was truly unreal. The best honeymoon location we could‚Äôve asked for! Thank you Cap Rocat team!!","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"hannah bates","rating":1,"text":"FOOD POISONING WITH HOSTILE RESPONSE\nI am writing to warn others about a recent (September 2025) visit.The service and hospitality were extremely disappointing and ultimately became hostile as the hotel became concerned about its risk exposure to a health incident for which I believe (but cannot confirm) it was responsible. For context and disclosure on the opinion contained in this review, I work in hospitality and have high expectations, and at the time of my stay at Cap Rocat I was 16 weeks pregnant and traveling alone. I feel obligated to warn all future guests who are considering this property about my experience.\nI acknowledge that it is difficult to identify the precise origin of food poisoning. In this case however, I am extremely confident my food poisoning came from food at Cap Rocat. After arriving and exploring the property in the afternoon, I ordered tagliatelle with shrimp to my room for an early dinner. Approximately four hours after my dinner, I began to experience nausea and within an hour of that vomiting began. Extreme symptoms continued for almost 10 hours after the initial onset. For the duration of my symptoms, I also requested sports drinks, water and ice, which the hotel promptly provided. Not being a health professional, and without access to my OBGYN in the United States to alleviate concerns or guide me through how I could get relief, I was extremely concerned about the health of my baby and to a lesser extent my own health.\nThe doctor who ultimately arrived had excellent bedside manner. Her exam confirmed an elevated heart rate, but she was not able to take my temperature because she had failed to bring a thermometer, explaining the hotel had not notified her about my complaints of a suspected fever. Tests for two types of flu and covid tests all returned negative. Upon finishing the exam, she informed me that after reviewing all of my symptoms she believed I was experiencing food poisoning but without a stool sample it would be impossible to be sure. She gave me anti-nausea medicine and a pregnancy safe fever reducer. She left, and symptoms began to go away. I was not provided a copy of her report.The first indication that the Hotel was concerned about their exposure to my illness came from my travel agent (and friend) who took the initiative to call the hotel when my symptoms were extreme and a doctor was not expected to arrive for many hours. He reported back to me that the hotel was denying all responsibility for my illness. This position continued through checkout, where the hotel maintained that the doctors report indicated that my symptoms were NOT the result of food poisoning and that *if it was food poisoning* it could not have come from the hotel‚Äôs kitchens because no other guests who were consuming the hotel‚Äôs food had reported issues. Furthermore, the medical report cited by the hotel has still not been provided to me despite repeated requests to the medical group contracted by the hotel. I was hopeful that Cap Rocat would offer *some* gesture to acknowledge my less than pleasant experience that I believe resulted from a lapse in their food safety protocols. This expectation was misplaced. Ultimately the hotel staff treated me with contempt, telling me at checkout that I never had a fever nor food poisoning according to the report, despite what the doctor told me directly, face to face, and the staff refused to take any responsibility for what was quite clearly food poisoning and offered no refund or discount, and no gesture to make up for an unpleasant stay, for which I am highly confident they are to blame.","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"AGNES SEOW YEAN","rating":1,"text":"No children allow. No children allow. Be mindful when making a booking with them if you are travelling with children . They turn you away no matter what and charge fully for your first night  with them but allow refund for the rest of the nights.\nThey don‚Äôt take kids in their restaurant or anything. disappointing ,yes. Coming back to explore again without kids ? Maybe .","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Mich O","rating":5,"text":"Amazing experience, I highly recommend coming here while in Mallorca. We came for lunch so that we could see the blue water and we were so happy we did. Service was impeccable, food was good! Views were amazing. This restaurant is definitely worth the visit. Even if you don‚Äôt like seafood, I would still come for the experience and scenery.","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"Alexandra Skeggs","rating":5,"text":"Such a lush experience. Highly recommend the sea club - need to make reservations in advance. Absolutely gorgeous setting for lunch. We arrived early and had a drink in their grand bar.","time":"3 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
