or":"John Wakefield","rating":5,"text":"Simply magnificent.\nVisited to enjoy afternoon tea on the terrace.\nThis hotel is magical - breathtaking views of the mountains, impeccable service, wonderful gardens, it simply oozes class and elegance.\nIt‚Äôs as if you enter a different world.\nWe did stay for 2 nights a few year ago to celebrate my birthday and have visited several times for afternoon tea- it‚Äôs one of  best hotels we have been to.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Levi Elekes","rating":4,"text":"It was a pleasant experience. The management team was probably the most attentive team we‚Äôve seen so far, making sure everything was okay. The fact that they provided water throughout the property to avoid using plastic was an amazing plus. The cleaning team did their job well, though sometimes they left bottles outside, which could fall and break.\n\nThe scenery is probably the most beautiful we‚Äôve ever seen. We received daily gifts, which was really nice, along with fresh fruit and flowers every day.\n\nHowever, the rooms and services didn‚Äôt quite match the price we paid. The restaurant we tried (Miro) was one of the weakest we‚Äôve been to ‚Äî there are far better options in Deia, so we ended up eating out most of the time.\n\nThe sunset cruise is a must and a really great addition. Overall, the experience was very nice, but we don‚Äôt feel it justified the price compared to other places we‚Äôve stayed at for a similar cost.","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"sydney allen","rating":5,"text":"We just left from our stay at the La Residencia and it was nothing short of perfection. My husband and I just spent the beginning of our honeymoon with them and not only is this property absolutely stunning, the service and attention to detail is unmatched. From start to finish their staff is unbelievably kind, professional, and genuine and truly made our honeymoon better than we could have imagined. Not to mention the food across all the restaurants is fantastic. El Olivo was amazing and such a unique experience but our favorite meal was at Miro. I couldn‚Äôt recommend this place more!! Worth every penny!","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Antoine Eliot","rating":5,"text":"While visiting Dei√† with my partner, we were eager to experience La Residencia, A Belmond Hotel.\nWe also stopped by the bar, where the experience was truly exceptional thanks to the manager, Jorge. We started inside before he kindly found us a beautiful table on the terrace ‚Äî the perfect setting.\nA special mention for the Old Fashioned, without question the best I‚Äôve ever had in my life.","time":"2 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
