 Resort</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN2bXOUpXM3H-yuczEfRJBNK4C4N4E1cDHACBNgeNVfwRj57MP4vxgeBoz8BAJo3sQ9CkWRz5lPO45cJOmHPpQghlxnNgqIZTjXsZYZw7xei98k24jgVpiPdah_GzyImVwo0mO00cUFeJk9cdTf9vfK_6PKoKGgtEUoVd1n1ebsnQAl3hiCPvWT7xaY64PVc1ELwRMEv6k1bdEB8KdDHQnRR-mI_vCg4FDwg37yalVnnwSn8lTlQc3I9jdCtm8w_9QDoPNOg2ofR8a8pgIeDiLzo127Gx1C0pLZBIgfZoy7p6Q","width":480,"height":320,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/109399554085109825590\">The St. Regis Mardavall Mallorca Resort</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN38XiVy7Usg4qf027tsx6xPMFH8ZyjLUPmJAO6IjdS0xzM8a5RHbpwnldTqDiGIX2SfzS35bUSxmJbCKG-5Fw8Y6nVNp86DdAbbEC3Z5CRbIwyMIXdF-DduqTo5AFd2CO0qcEJQHpSfNth9YCOu621Eezsl2GhB0_goZ1r8m7OvJg_KI82NXzJgF5_u-Woc7EY1lkJeyVeoymrgDPnB-oL4ITQel_hG1JZWFWTc1UF3nybYPViIyWklYIrPkEE56wMol09VG-60qzRdCIH5HIyCqvmLDoKjqJ5lVhngG4w7sA","width":480,"height":320,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/109399554085109825590\">The St. Regis Mardavall Mallorca Resort</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Heather VanDerheyden","rating":5,"text":"This was by far the best hotel I‚Äôve booked in quite some time. The grounds were beautiful, the food was exquisite, and the spa was clean with endless amenities. The staff was unbelievably attentive and helpful. We lost our sunglasses in a cab and they tracked down the driver for us! The hotel is conveniently located for day trips into Palma and S√≥ller, and located right near the most fabulous port with top notch restaurants! Would highly recommend.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"B B. Alo","rating":2,"text":"The location of the hotel is excellent, but unfortunately the service and most of the staff are disappointing, except for the reception team who were welcoming and attentive. The butler service was extremely poor and I would not recommend it at all. Breakfast was acceptable, but the service was very slow.\n\nOne of the most concerning issues we noticed was clear discrimination against Arabs, from the breakfast area to the restaurants. Staff seemed to treat non-Arab guests much better, which was very unpleasant.\n\nThe garden-view rooms were uncomfortable, with many flying insects due to the garden area. Considering the price, I do not recommend this hotel ‚Äî there are definitely better options available.","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Andrew Reinstatler","rating":5,"text":"Top notch service all around. Absolutely loving our time here. After a couple of days, you really start to get to know the staff, and everyone has been superb. The butler service is fantastic, the food is fantastic, and the wait staff is fantastic.\n\nI‚Äôm not sure what that previous review is even from, but no way it‚Äôs about this place. I can attest to that.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Ludwig Brundin","rating":5,"text":"A million thx to Yaiza & Ramiroüôèüèª\n\nJust wow. The St. Regis Bar is pure magic ‚Äî where sophistication meets fun in the best way possible. From the moment you walk in, you‚Äôre treated like royalty. The atmosphere is elegant but never stuffy, the cocktails are absolute masterpieces, and the service? Flawless.\n\nWe had high expectations, and somehow they were exceeded. Every drink was a showstopper ‚Äî creative, beautifully presented, and perfectly balanced. The staff clearly love what they do and made the whole experience personal and memorable.\n\nAlready dreaming of our next visit. If you‚Äôre in town and want to treat yourself, this is the place. Cheers to unforgettable nights at the St. Regis Bar! üç∏üî•","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"LDP","rating":5,"text":"Wow! What an amazing resort the St. Regis Mardavall Mallorca is! A majestic  grand lady with beautiful grounds, great rooms, romantic fabulous dining options and most importantly a top tier staff, always eager to take care of you. Every single person we encountered from housekeeping,dining, bell hops, reception and concierge desk couldn‚Äôt have tried harder to make us feel welcome. They were great at anticipating our every need.A special thanks to Marguerite, Jose, Christine and Alecia. The other plus about the St Regis is its optimum location on the island. Being there you feel secluded in a beautiful paradise, but are a short taxi ride to Palma and a delightful scenic ride to Deia, Valldemossa and Banyalbafur. We have been to 64 countries, 47 states and this is one of the most beautiful,places we have been, as well as a great hotel! A heartfelt thanks!","time":"3 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
