t what truly made the experience unforgettable was the amazing team behind the scenes. Lucia and Eli, the venue-based planners, are absolute superstars. From the very first email to the last dance of the night, they were supportive, responsive, and incredibly talented. Their attention to detail, creative ideas, and calm professionalism meant we were able to relax and fully enjoy every moment. Nothing was ever too much trouble, and they made sure everything ran seamlessly on the day.\n\nOur guests are still talking about how stunning the venue was and how well-organised everything felt ‚Äì and that‚Äôs entirely thanks to Lucia and Eli.\n\nIf you‚Äôre considering getting married in Mallorca, Finca Son Berga is everything you could want and more. We feel so lucky to have celebrated our day there and will treasure the memories forever. Thank you from the bottom of our hearts! üíõ","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"C Bryson","rating":5,"text":"Wow!!! There are no words to describe this incredible venue!\n\nFrom the moment we visited Son Berga for the first time, we knew this venue was the one for us! The feeling we got when we stepped out of our hire car and were greeted by the amazing Eli, we just had that magical feeling!\n\nEli & Lucia, who work here, are two ladies who go above and beyond to make sure everything goes perfect for their couples. They helped us with the planning, booking the best suppliers on the island and were there to run our special day where they had everything timed to perfection and their calm and kind aura was a joy to be around.\n\nWe had several video calls and visited the venue in person a couple of times - the ladies always had everything under control and made everything stress free. The technical visit day was a dream - where we got to visit the showroom and choose all of our decor and finer details. The finca itself - interiors and exteriors are absolutely immaculate and Eli takes so much pride in her ‚Äúbaby.‚Äù Every bit of stone work is perfect and all flowers were in full bloom - it was absolutely stunning. The backdrop for the ceremony/aisle walk is breathtaking and looks like something from a movie.\n\nI don‚Äôt think we will ever come down from cloud 9 after getting married at the beautiful Finca Son Berga and even our guests are still talking about the venue and the food by Vicky Pulgarin - I will leave a seperate review on this because - WOW!!\n\nWe are looking at photos and in disbelief that this day was ours. We have memories to last a lifetime and we genuinely already can‚Äôt wait to go back to Mallorca and visit our new friends Eli & Lucia.","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"Beth Macdonald","rating":5,"text":"We had our wedding at Son Berga in August 2025 - it was the best day of our lives! Son Berga was the first wedding venue we saw in Mallorca and we instantly knew we wanted to get married there, not only for how stunning the finca and its surroundings are, but also for how lovely and welcoming the team there are.\n\nThroughout the entire process Lucia and Eli went above and beyond to help create a day that felt unique and personalised to us and was everything we could have wished for.\n\nWe cannot thank the entire team enough and would wholeheartedly recommend Son Berga to anyone getting married in Mallorca!","time":"2 weeks ago"},{"author":"Selina Diep","rating":5,"text":"We recently had our wedding here on the 24th August 2024 and wow what a wedding it was!\n\nThis venue is absolutely stunning. We remember it was the last venue we went to visit with our wedding planner but we knew immediately- this was the one. The venue is huge and meant we could have different elements of the wedding in different areas from the ceremony to the cocktail area to the dinner area to the after party. The flow was brilliant. Ellie, the owner, made it even more better as she was so lovely and welcoming. She came out to greet us many times, she made the experience a lot more personable.\n\nWe love this venue so much!","time":"a year ago"},{"author":"Max Hannon","rating":5,"text":"Title: A Majestic Wedding Experience at Son Berga, Majorca\n\nSon Berga in Majorca, Spain, proved to be an exceptional wedding venue that left a lasting impression on me. From the moment I arrived, I was captivated by the magical atmosphere and the creation of unforgettable memories. While not in Italy, the scenery at Son Berga evoked images reminiscent of a scene from \"The Godfather,\" with its stunning backdrop nestled between two majestic mountains that felt almost biblical.\n\nThe setting at Son Berga was truly awe-inspiring. The picturesque beauty of the surrounding landscape provided a romantic and enchanting ambiance for the wedding celebration. The lush greenery, rolling hills, and the panoramic views of the mountains created a breathtaking backdrop that added a touch of grandeur to the occasion. It was a feast for the senses, immersing guests in a captivating experience that will be cherished forever.\n\nThe attention to detail and impeccable organization of the wedding at Son Berga were truly commendable. Every aspect of the event, from the ceremony to the reception, was flawlessly executed. The staff demonstrated professionalism, ensuring that everything ran smoothly and seamlessly. Their commitment to delivering an extraordinary wedding experience was evident, and their expertise contributed to the overall success of the celebration.\n\nThe venue itself exuded elegance and charm. The carefully curated spaces, adorned with tasteful decor and subtle touches, added an air of sophistication to the occasion. The reception area, with its exquisite design and breathtaking views, provided the perfect setting for guests to dine, dance, and celebrate the union of two souls. It was a testament to the meticulous planning and thoughtfulness put into creating an unforgettable experience for all.\n\nThe culinary experience at Son Berga was equally remarkable. The delectable cuisine served during the wedding celebration was a true delight for the senses. From the exquisite appetizers to the mouthwatering main courses and decadent desserts, every dish was expertly crafted and bursting with flavor. The talented chefs showcased their culinary prowess, leaving guests with a lasting impression of gastronomic excellence.\n\nOverall, my experience at Son Berga was nothing short of extraordinary. The venue''s majestic surroundings, impeccable organization, and exceptional culinary offerings created a wedding celebration that surpassed all expectations. It was a testament to the power of love, bringing together family and friends in a setting that felt straight out of a fairytale.\n\nI will forever cherish the magical memories created at Son Berga. If you''re in search of a wedding venue that combines natural beauty, impeccable service, and a touch of enchantment, I wholeheartedly recommend considering Son Berga in Majorca, Spain. It is a place where dreams come true and where the start of a beautiful journey can be celebrated in the most extraordinary way.\n\nIf you found my review helpful, please give it a üëç and follow me on Google Maps for more insightful tips around the world. Cheers to unforgettable wedding celebrations!","time":"2 years ago"}]'::jsonb,
