ting":5,"text":"We had our wedding at Elixir in September 2025 and we could not recommend it enough for any couples that are looking for a venue on the Island.\n\nThe setting is beautiful, the team are incredible and the support that you get from the Leah and Vikki in the run up to the day gave us the peace of mind we needed when planning a destination wedding. All of this combined made our wedding day one to remember.\n\nI do believe one of the main selling points of this venue (beyond the gorgeous views) is the team on hand. They were exceptional and we have had many comments from our guests which demonstrates the lasting impression they have had. Each team member was attentive, personable and generally invested in ensuring that everyone was having the best day possible. If you are looking for somewhere where children can be accommodated for, we would definitely recommend the Kids Corner option that is available through the venue which was such a great touch for our younger guests and their parents!\n\nWe also could not fault the food & drinks on offer either and again is still something our guests are raving about a month on!\n\nif you are looking for a venue that captures the best of Ibiza - modern, stylish and fun - this is one to have a look at!\n\nThank you for hosting us and for a memorable wedding weekend!","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"Zoe Moore-Williams","rating":5,"text":"Woah! Elixir have something truly special, nestled up high on that hilltop‚Ä¶ what a venue, what a team!\nPlanning our wedding here was a total breeze, I still can‚Äôt believe it was so easy. Vickki & Leah are the dream team with communication and planning & Lou and the on-the-day team were SENSATIONAL on our actual wedding day. They honestly couldn‚Äôt do enough for us, they were simply brilliant! It‚Äôs been 3 weeks since our big day and our guests are still talking about the amazing food and drinks Elixir served up. I cannot thank you guys enough for making our day so magical, my only wish is that we could do it all over again! It was 10/10 on every level! Big love, Zoe & Paris xx","time":"6 months ago"},{"author":"Shalina Thomson","rating":5,"text":"The most MAGICAL venue for what was the best day of our lives!! We got married on 13.07.23 and it was unforgettable!!\n\nClear blue skies, a stunning colourful sunset, beautiful views of magnetic Es Vedra, a picture perfect bay to look upon, excitement in the air‚Ä¶. It was just UNREAL!!\n\nThe moment you walk through the doors it takes your breath away!!! The first time we went to Elixir was the day before the wedding and I burst into tears of pure joy. It was literally everything we had hoped for and much more.\n\nThe backdrop is second to none but the service that Elixir provide is seamless and perfect. The decor is taken care of with precision, we had beautiful roses and a gorgeous table design. We had a fully vegetarian meal, our guests still rave about the delicious and plentiful tapas boards, the gorgeous starters and the mouth watering desserts. The drinks package kept on giving and we were all spoilt with endless cold drinks to cool us down in the heatwave that was our wedding day!\n\nVickki and the team went out of their way to make our dreams come to life. We wanted a seating  plan with a bespoke design - cocktail glasses presented in a beautiful display, each with guest name and table name attached (see photo) - it turned out perfect! It was so touching that she came to greet us at the meal and had personally seen us at the ceremony, we could feel how much she cares about her guests!\n\nMauricio met us the day before and was so calming and reassuring. What a beautiful soul! Every single one of our many requests was met with a smile and a can- do attitude. Nothing was too much trouble to achieve and we felt completely supported in making the day exactly how we had envisaged. He was seamless in his efforts to organise our ceremony and our guests and keep the events of the day running smoothly.\n\nOne highlight of the day was taking a walk along Cala Codolar beach as newly weds, a glass of ice cold champagne in hand and the feint buzz of our guests enjoying themselves on the Elixir terrace above. The sun was setting over the breathtaking horizon and our hearts were filled with LOVE.\n\nWhat we would give to do it all again!! Thank you so much Elixir for making our special day truly amazing xxx","time":"11 months ago"},{"author":"Youri Claessens Photography","rating":5,"text":"I had the pleasure of photographing a lot of weddings at this stunning venue and I have to say, I can highly recommend this venue. The location was simply breathtaking, with panoramic views of the sparkling sea and the rugged Ibiza coastline. The venue itself was beautifully designed, with elegant, modern decor that perfectly complemented the natural surroundings.\n\nThe staff were incredibly helpful and attentive, making sure that everything ran smoothly throughout the entire event. From the catering to the entertainment, every aspect of the wedding was top-notch and flawlessly executed.\n\nThank you so much to the amazing team of Elixir who makes my work as a wedding photographer also easier. They take care that the couple and their guests have an amazing time, and they never disappointed :)","time":"2 years ago"},{"author":"Michaela Churchill-Cooper","rating":5,"text":"We celebrated our wedding here in September 2023 and I‚Äôm struggling to find the words for just how perfect Elixir and all of the team were. From our very first enquiry their communication was excellent, nothing was too much trouble and every interaction felt like talking with a friend. The venue''s attention to detail was flawless, I can‚Äôt thank the team enough for everything they did to help create our dream wedding.\n\nThe venue staff were all amazing. Mauricio went above and beyond to help with anything we needed all day, I‚Äôve never been made to feel so special. Every bride deserves to feel like that on their wedding day! Louise was so attentive and friendly - we were taken care of all day without having to worry about a thing. The food was simply flawless and all of our guests commented on how exceptional the food was!\n\nI could go on, but no words will ever be enough to show our gratitude. The whole day was so perfect and unique - better than we could have ever imagined.\n\nThank you for a truly magical day!","time":"2 years ago"}]'::jsonb,
