 Sadoveanu","rating":3,"text":"If by mistake your stay is during Palms cleaning or grass cutting for sure you will not sleep starting with 7:30. This is really unacceptable especially when they are asking for 550 euro / night. Too bad that they are not thinking at their clients, the place is beautiful!\nLater edit, now after several weeks from our vacation and the frustration of not sleeping gone, I decided to change to 3 stars - the place is too beautiful to have their scor decreased -\nDear hotel management please take care of your clients in the days of grass cutting - it is really annoying to wake up at 7:30 in huge noise.","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"joanna ramonell","rating":5,"text":"Magical Orange Tree Summer Garden Opening at Atzar√≥\n\nIt was everything we love about Ibiza ‚Äì authentic, elegant, and effortlessly cool.\nDreamy garden atmosphere with candlelight, citrus trees, and tastful authentic flower arrangements that added a timeless, Ibizan charm.\nThe food was divine too ‚Äì never had melt in your mouth lamb chops like that! fresh, flavourful, and beautifully presented. Cocktails were elevated and on point too, But the special highlight? The flamenco performance ‚Äì passionate, soulful, and done with such grace and style. It was so lovely to see it celebrated in such a pure yet contemporary 2025 way.\nBravo to Atzar√≥ and the lovely Leanne of course for creating something that feels both grounded in Ibiza‚Äôs spirit and effortlessly luxurious. Can‚Äôt wait to be back x","time":"6 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
