g, the kind of place where you instantly feel relaxed and happy the moment you walk in. The atmosphere, the view, the soft warmth of the evening, the music‚Ä¶ everything came together beautifully.\n\nThe location alone is absolutely breathtaking, the kind of place that instantly gives you goosebumps. The service was incredible, not just attentive, but genuinely heartfelt. We were lucky to have Yordi as our private butler, and what a beautiful soul he is. He made us feel completely at ease, cared for us in every detail, and added so much warmth to the evening.\n\nThe menu, created especially for us with the freshest products of the day, was a sensational journey. Every dish was a surprise, every bite full of flavor, and the wine pairings were simply perfect, the kind that make you close your eyes for a moment just to enjoy it fully.\n\nHonestly, this was nothing short of a magical night in August 2025. One word: unforgettable. We will 100% be coming back. Without exaggeration, this is one of the best restaurants we have ever visited.. If not the single best dining experience of our lives.","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Jaskiran Kaur","rating":4,"text":"The most stunning dinner view I have ever seen. Breathtaking.\nBut do reserve the place well in advance.\nIt gets prettier when it starts to get dark and lights come out.\nFor a place that pretty, the food is surprisingly good as well.\nWe ordered beetroot starter which had refreshing and fresh flavours.\nFor mains we ordered the Risotto and Spaghetti. The Risotto was exceptional as it had a strong flavour of truffle.\nWhile the vegan options are limited but the food was good.\n\nWhile the desserts looked really appetising, we didn‚Äôt have space for alot so we went for an affogato. This was my first time ever and we loved the taste.\n\nWhile the place is on the expensive side, but it‚Äôs truly worth every penny you spend here.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Vittoria Brondin","rating":4,"text":"This beachfront restaurant is truly a hidden gem in Ibiza, offering a charming setting and a memorable dining experience. While the adjacent beach area could benefit from better maintenance and cleanliness, the restaurant itself is well worth a visit for lunch or dinner.\n\nThe food was absolutely delicious,flavorful, well-prepared, and beautifully presented. However, the portions were on the smaller side, especially considering the higher price point. Typically, Spanish cuisine is known for its generous servings, so this was a bit unexpected.\n\nBe prepared for high pricing, but keep in mind that you''re paying for the overall experience, not just the meal. The ambiance, location, and attentive service contribute to the value.\n\nA special mention goes to Stefania, our waitress, who was incredibly friendly and helpful.\n\nWhile the restaurant itself is lovely, it''s not ideal if you''re looking for a budget-friendly beach day. The sunbeds and umbrellas are quite expensive, and unfortunately, the sea in this area wasn''t very clean during our visit. I would strongly recommend more attention to maintaining the beach area to fully complement the otherwise excellent restaurant experience.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Carl Birkenshaw","rating":5,"text":"We had a fantastic dining experience here ‚Äì the service was superb, and Berta was the perfect host, attentive and warm, making sure nothing was too much trouble.\n\nThe food was excellent from start to finish. I started with the clams, which were fresh, full of flavour, and perfectly cooked in a delicate broth. Clare had the croquettes ‚Äì crisp on the outside and deliciously soft inside ‚Äì a real highlight. For mains, Clare enjoyed the black squid ink risotto with scallops, which was rich, creamy, and beautifully presented, while I had the veal chop with homemade fries, cooked to perfection and full of flavour.\n\nWe finished with coffee, which rounded off what was a wonderful meal. The quality of the ingredients, the presentation, and the relaxed yet professional service made the whole experience memorable.\n\nHighly recommended","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Olivier Populaire","rating":5,"text":"One of Ibiza‚Äôs finest restaurants. Amante is truly one of the most magical dining spots in Ibiza. Nestled on a quiet cliffside overlooking the sea, it offers an atmosphere that feels effortlessly romantic and refined.\n\nThe service, the food, the vibe, all is just top notch! You‚Äôll be able to enjoy any dish you eat here. Amante isn‚Äôt just a restaurant; it‚Äôs an experience. We‚Äôll definitely be coming back!\n\nThanks to all of the staff, specifically Francesca, for providing us a wonderful evening!!","time":"2 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
