--XNCgXSBZD7pzhYP15qBCMidEa0GrU6uJZ81IOtmmduWA8eYHo8LOAy247hVJsbVTy8OEkDiANJlaZo_t7t5ibRN4irXGmqAxzgFtu0W0B7oUzOOKL72f1CUk5RnTmmQohlLi1Yr0zFOdMcVgwG-72knx75MrO_P5LLrXT1wJZdE1ZZlFx6lacvGLGhNIdmCs-d8","width":1920,"height":1080,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/113507434537827862538\">Agroturismo Can Gall</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN17afhog8w-UGTM2EAas2O5TMX_OkzR8DHB48FG87bv09L6cIFsGV4Y9k3yL7Y_ArzkZvatDIYzF1JlReNFq7RtPZpccw6LDouCJUaUFnF1Blv7sT1SmEOZVw6qPuCx0oegp2bR1X16B6fc6AIF_XMs4jkQjx6LeJe-v0kh5QWyYVZywWLLBcnbNTg4-Nu7LgZRXHSSjOh5mMZi3YZv0eNTcpaOXhk1x_asPH304HgpvZGk7-ahtVuHwVmgKwOXr1zlqoCbMxnJdgz5d2VbdYZP1FWKWmFySttaOy6_ZjQ","width":3954,"height":2224,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/113507434537827862538\">Agroturismo Can Gall</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Arnald","rating":5,"text":"I had an amazing time play and staying in Cal Gall, it''s a gorgeous venue and really unique in Ibiza. My stay there was for a wedding playing saxophone and it really was wonderful.","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"April Clarke","rating":5,"text":"We just hosted the most incredible wedding at this uniquely rustic hotel on the beautiful island of Ibiza.\n\nSanti, Ana, Rachel & team could not do enough for not only us as the couple but all guests staying with us. All guests complimented the ease of the place and instantly felt at home, others had recommended it to family and friends whilst still at the hotel.\n\nRachel‚Äôs attention to detail and drive to make the bride feel at ease throughout the lead up and planning is superb. I was so relaxed I was sure I‚Äôd missed something but she keeps you honest and gives you a nudge on securing suppliers (which are in a league of their own).\n\nMy words can‚Äôt do justice to how it made myself and guests feel having somewhere so organised yet relaxed to make the whole weekend enjoyable.\n\nIf you are debating whether to choose this as your wedding venue I will promise you, you  won‚Äôt be disappointed.\n\nThanks so much for the most memorable time.\n\nWe hope to come back and see you soon.","time":"a year ago"},{"author":"Laura Andrews","rating":5,"text":"Wow, where do we start.\nWe were lucky enough to be shown this venue by my mother in law when searching for somewhere in Ibiza to hold our wedding. Can Gall is a little hidden gem, only to be found by those lucky enough. As all the other reviews say Santi, Ana and Rachel, along with Augustine and the team are incredible and quite honestly make you feel like you are royalty whilst you are there.\nWe originally visited in Aug last year to view for the first time along with some other venues and as soon as the gates opened to reveal Can Gall we both knew this was the one. Rachel has been outstanding throughout the last 12 months helping us to plan the wedding of our dreams. Nothing is too much for her and she guides you through what is required with ease. I could go into reams of detail about how fab she is but there isn‚Äôt room on here!\nThe same for Santi and Ana, they really do make you and all of our guests feel so special from the second you arrive. Nothing is too much and they work around the clock to do what they can for you. From the seamless check in, the stunning meal the eve before the wedding to the pool party the day after. We honestly can‚Äôt thank them enough and are desperate to return and visit again soon.\nThere really isn‚Äôt enough room here for me to tell you how fantastic they are but if you are considering booking and have any questions I‚Äôd be more than happy for you to message me.\n\nIf you find this venue, you really are one of the lucky ones.\n\nThank you to Santi, Ana, Rachel and team for everything. Last weekend really was the wedding of dreams for us.\nLaura & Ben","time":"a year ago"},{"author":"Ian Gordon","rating":5,"text":"Just enjoyed the most amazing wedding for my daughter. She found the venue (and obviously her new husband and I agreed!) but could not find fault. The setting is beautiful and authentic old charm. Santi is an amazing host -lovely man where nothing is too much trouble - and a great chef. A 4 night event for us - meal on the Thursday was excellent chicken thighs , chill by the pool Friday , wedding Saturday ( sun came out bang on time after torrential rain!) so able to be outdoors. Is ideal covered area with open sides if the worst happens!  Nothing was too much trouble. The drinks packs take a bit of getting used to -have to guess what might consume ( although more was available to buy). We had a lot of soft drinks left including water - alcohol however was a different matter!  Tip. Get guests to restock mini bar from soft drinks package not drunk or you pay for water from the mini bar   There are extra snacks available on non actual wedding day - pizza etc - which was helpful tho cost can add up.\nBreakfast served from 9am ( civilised !). Outside catering used for actual wedding.\n\nDo highly recommend. Easy taxi to anywhere on Ibiza. Thanks Santi and team.  Sadly won‚Äôt be back!","time":"a year ago"},{"author":"John Hedley","rating":5,"text":"Many reviews have described Can Gall and to be honest they are all true. Santi and Anna, the owners of Gan Gall, are the most honest hardworking hotel proprietors my wife and I have come  across. No fault could be found from the cleanliness of the rooms to the perfect presentation of the exterior facilities.\nNothing is to much trouble for any of the staff as they have only the comfort of the guests in mind. All we had to do was enjoy the piece and quiet of such bountiful surroundings, which there was in abundance.\nThank you for a wonderful stay and sincerely hope to be back soon.","time":"2 years ago"}]'::jsonb,
