nd quick. First holiday we felt like we''d lost weight, which we don''t know how, could be all the fat held on by stress was released! Thanks Cas Gasi team for a wonderful stay","time":"2 years ago"},{"author":"C Chan","rating":5,"text":"Having previously only stayed in villas on the island, this is as close to that experience as you''re going to get in a hotel.  Although the room decor is dated and the hard fittings like the bathroom are not very luxurious, the room amenities like the linen, toiletries, robes, slippers, coffee machine, kettle, beach bag & towels etc are top quality and the aircon units are modern and quiet.  The best thing about the hotel though is the size of the facilities and common areas vs the number of rooms.  It has all the facilities of a much larger luxury property but only shared by 18 rooms, so there are loads of places to hang out and you never have to worry about not getting a sunbed by the pool or reserving a table for lunch or dinner.  It''s also in a great location- completely peaceful and rural, but only a 20-25 min taxi ride to ibiza town.  Was great to be able to go clubbing easily and then return to such a peaceful environment to recover.","time":"a year ago"},{"author":"danuta freeman","rating":5,"text":"This is an incredible place. Location is central, food is amazing, rooms are authentic.  But‚Ä¶ the real highlight of our stay was Cali. His kindness and  incredible island knowledge tapped into our vibe. His recs are faultless! He is a gem. Thank you for an amazing stay","time":"a year ago"},{"author":"Juan Via√±o","rating":5,"text":"Cas Gasi provides a peaceful retreat with its charming atmosphere and tasteful decor. The tranquility of the countryside setting is complemented by the warm hospitality of the hostess, Margaret, whose kindness and attention to detail make every stay special. It''s a perfect haven for those seeking peace, beauty, and exceptional service.","time":"a year ago"},{"author":"Matthias De Clercq","rating":5,"text":"My name is Charlie, my parents and I had a lovely stay in cas gasi. It was my first time in Ibiza and I definitely will come back.\nCas Gasi was a home away from home where I could experience all the magic. The beautiful garden the colourful flowers and the fresh fruits every morning at breakfast.\nWhile I was napping my parents could enjoy the stunning swimming pool, a nice facial or a relaxing massage from the island best therapists. Im still more of a milky girl myself but my parents were gushing over the amazing food they had at dinner.\nI want to thank all lovely staff and nice guests for all the smiles they put on my face.\nI will treasure my new memories for a long time !\nThank you Cas Gasi from your youngest fan!","time":"a year ago"}]'::jsonb,
