ns, we knew our stay would be special‚Äîbut the hotel exceeded every expectation.\n\nThe staff upgraded us to a beautiful room for our anniversary and made us feel genuinely cherished. Their warmth, hospitality, and attention to detail were flawless. Room service was exceptional, the valet service was absolutely worth it, and every interaction felt personal and thoughtful.\n\nThe spa facilities were a complete indulgence‚Äîthe hammam, salt bath, and heated pool were such a treat that we barely wanted to leave the hotel for our planned activities. It truly felt like living inside a palace, wrapped in comfort, luxury, and care. The property itself is so stunning that it becomes an experience in its own right.\n\nWe had the most magical two days here. Anantara Villa Padierna Palace sets a standard far above typical European luxury and is easily one of the best hotels to stay at in Europe. A stay here is pure joy, and we left wishing we could‚Äôve stayed much longer.","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"mario ponikvar","rating":5,"text":"A very pleasant stay.  Very helpful personnel. Comfortable hotel, exquisite breakfast offer.  A nice spa (but why bathing suits in the saunas)?  Golf literally from hotel backyard.  Great courses.  An interesting variety of restaurants, tasty food (loved cr√™pes Suzette).  Missed a shoehorn in the room (maybe it just wasn‚Äôt replaced).","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Bogdan Stancu","rating":5,"text":"Our recent stay at VP was nothing short of extraordinary. From the moment we arrived, everything was handled with such care and attention to detail that it made us feel completely at ease. The setting is breathtaking, surrounded by the beauty of the Costa del Sol, and the entire property is designed to offer both comfort and elegance.\n\nMeals were consistently excellent, with a breakfast selection that truly stood out‚Äîfresh, diverse, and beautifully presented. The seafood options throughout our stay were especially memorable. The private beach area is a perfect retreat, providing everything you need for a relaxed day by the sea. Evenings were elevated by live music and talented performers, creating a wonderful atmosphere.\n\nWe want to extend our heartfelt thanks to Carlota, who always went above and beyond to ensure everything was arranged flawlessly, making our stay not only perfect but also truly personal. A special mention as well to Razvan, whose professionalism, kindness, and genuine care made us feel incredibly well looked after.\n\nIn short, this hotel exceeded all of our expectations and gave our family a week we will never forget. A truly exceptional place for anyone looking to enjoy the best of the Costa del Sol.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Luis Antonio da Silva J√§ger","rating":5,"text":"We have spent one week in paradise. All aspects of this hotel are perfect: it is situated in a fantastic area with beautiful landscapes, the staff are friendly and always prompt to serve the guests, and the restaurants offer excellent food. The breakfast is the best I‚Äôve seen so far, with a wide variety of fruits, juices, and other fresh, high-quality options.\n\nThe hotel has a private area on the beach, with everything you need to enjoy a wonderful time by the sea. I especially loved the excellent seafood options. In the bars and restaurants, you can enjoy great music and professional singers.\n\nIn summary, my family and I had a fantastic time at Anantara! It is a very good choice for enjoying the Costa del Sol.","time":"4 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
