":"It''s just been our one year anniversary of my husband and I after getting married at the hacienda, and we wanted to leave a review.\n\nThe hacienda is beautiful with all of the natural florals. The grounds are kept immaculate, and the service is incredibly attentive. We were guided at every step for our wedding preparation, and having the place to ourselves for the weekend was so very special.\n\nEveryone was so pleased with the morning breakfast outside your room, and the multiple pools gave everyone enough space to find the hangout energy they were looking for.\n\nThe food was incredible at the hacienda. Our favorite was the BBQ buffet they do, which we had for one of the nights. Absolutely incredible.\n\nWe were so glad to have our wedding around this time, (June 1), where the sunflowers were in full bloom. It truly looked like a dream and everyone still speaks about it!\n\nWe hope our review helps anyone wondering if this is a great venue for your wedding, and let this review tell you that it absolutely is and will be so very unforgettable!\n\nWe can''t wait to go back (and absolutely plan to) as well to visit the hacienda, as it now holds a special place in ours and our families hearts üíï","time":"7 months ago"},{"author":"Harry Scott","rating":5,"text":"We were told about Hacienda de San Rafael by a friend who owns a travel agency, otherwise we would never have known about it. The Hacienda is off the beaten track, in the middle of farm country but is one of the most welcoming places we have ever stayed. And the food is amazing! Momma is the inspiration for the recipes but it is Anthony, the co-owner, son and perfect host who makes the entire experience so memorable. From breakfast on your porch outside your room to wonderful dinners either in the dining room or in warm weather, around the different outdoor dining areas of the hacienda. Highly recommend if you are lucky enough to be in this part of Andalusia.","time":"8 months ago"},{"author":"Gary Yang","rating":5,"text":"The villas were stunning. We stayed in the pool villas just off the main house and they looked newly built and artfully designed interior. The level of service was spectacular with food service, room cleaning, and even just making sure every lawn chair had a towel on it at all times. The staff were very helpful even with our language barrier. We were lucky to catch the sunflower fields in the back and we could not stop taking it in.\n\nI don‚Äôt understand how this only says it‚Äôs a 3-star hotel because our stay was clearly a 4-star at a minimum. Highly highly recommend.","time":"a year ago"},{"author":"Steve Mangano","rating":5,"text":"An absolutely magical place.  Staff is incredibly accommodating and this is truly hospitality at its finest.  We enjoyed every moment.  They have curated fantastic tours and we especially enjoyed the sherry tasting.  Add several nights here as part of your stay in Andalusia.","time":"a year ago"},{"author":"Victoria Glenn","rating":5,"text":"My husband and I are so happy we got married here! We are from Colorado, USA which is known for having beautiful wedding venues so you could say we have high expectations. My husband spent some time as a child in Spain so we decided to do a destination wedding abroad and one of his friends who is a local in Sevilla suggested the Hacienda de San Rafael. We did our wedding in June so all the flowers were in bloom and we had amazing pictures in the sunflower field next to our reception area. The staff was amazing and definitely played a large part in the tranquil atmosphere at the Hacienda. Everyone was so welcoming and I felt they were putting a lot of effort into making our stay special! I didn‚Äôt have a single worry the whole day which most brides cannot say. The food was fresh and delicious! The rooms were cozy and spacious yet intimate. I couldn‚Äôt have asked for a better stay and hope to be back sometime in the future.","time":"3 years ago"}]'::jsonb,
