rd as I did wandering the ancient halls and rooms filled with old art and furniture. Incredibly well renovated and lovingly maintained inside and out. Nothing like storming the gates of a 700 year old castle to get some appetizers after the wedding service","time":"9 months ago"},{"author":"Claudia Postigo","rating":5,"text":"At The Planner Co we love Castillo de Batres. It''s one of the few castles near Madrid to get married. It''s recently refurbish and the areas are stunning for a wedding. They work with a great list of caterings to pick from and their team is fantastic. We are very excited for our next wedding soon.","time":"a year ago"},{"author":"Erin Marcelo","rating":5,"text":"I can‚Äôt say enough about the incredible experience we had hosting our wedding at this venue‚Äîit was nothing short of magical. From the moment we arrived, the staff went above and beyond to help us bring our vision to life. Their kindness, patience, and attention to detail made the entire planning process so much smoother. Every question we had was answered promptly, and they made sure we were always comfortable and confident with every decision.\n\nOur wedding was a beautiful blend of Spanish and American traditions, and the venue was the perfect backdrop for our celebration. Both our American and Spanish guests were absolutely blown away by the stunning castle setting, with many commenting that it was one of the most beautiful venues they had ever seen.\n\nIf you‚Äôre looking for a venue that offers not only breathtaking beauty but also exceptional service, I would wholeheartedly recommend this place. It made our special day even more unforgettable, and we‚Äôre so grateful to the staff for making it all come together seamlessly.","time":"9 months ago"},{"author":"Heather Sye","rating":5,"text":"Wedding of my dreams.\n\nEvery detail, every provider, every moment came together so perfectly, I couldn''t ask for anything more.\n\nWe will forever cherish our Castle. Thank you!","time":"