82845424658\">Juan Pablo Morales Sarmiento</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN33D3br-DFGYra0QNLNEMvN-ZZnHg6TZOSQ71v-r0WJqOydM_JvNJgexQCNg1PPJlzVfL5IazDGP5631vnfj4jMOugWv43daGVbuZfBTraE3H31z58-xgFQLLKyZ8_FP64oMn3EngMsADsho2HdyahvHRTEncrODB7t82JuhblimhcQnWXyQbIRfIRaQff0-Tm3UiUMbME4fhH1JxLGAmSECI4gyD_IbPwpJye9x5O7gJ9swREf6ByhTPEajbW71Bbe6t6rIwqsrP9KL3a7tXUYmu3o-C_FQTF-c4ECq5y1sw","width":780,"height":900,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/103400088284053067170\">Castillo de Vi√±uelas</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN36eUvmURVpSZnWF4woMJKy-A1zum5TjYo2nr0KjKzNWrsbxb35vIr5oSrfadtjRnHiO-fowlzkMqYTQiMsymfhlq7iHMIM5XT8O-frgeOepZgmCWOL_oTZsimzsbAT5HeuJ4MqpzewAhjr2IwQPUo4DZUAZ7ii01U3QCClRk1rPje_yOc3etp5b2YAWZ0vdV0MtRVU4UVWq4kbaIHZcPqxIwRuqY0qucPeBKtYOXNJCUoUdGbu5D7EkIIxg5SjwdvBAid6Gxf5GO6ENcWEqn6XidCn92cn7rGK7zg5ybtwOw","width":1280,"height":720,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/103400088284053067170\">Castillo de Vi√±uelas</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Monica Alexandru","rating":4,"text":"Closed for visits for now.","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"ANTONIO CASTRO","rating":5,"text":"Wonderful!!!","time":"7 months ago"},{"author":"MARIA DOLORES PRADA SOTILLO","rating":1,"text":"The venue is very beautiful and idyllic. If you don''t, the glass gazebo where you''ll be celebrating your wedding will burn down in less than a month. The event company (Visi, Ver√≥nica) gives you very good words and tells you not to worry, that they''ll do everything possible to make everything perfect. What they give you is a plastic tent, which is what you absolutely didn''t want, which is why you ordered the glass gazebo. The thing is, THERE WAS NO CONSIDERATION ON THE PART OF THE COMPANY AND NO PRICE ADJUSTMENT (apparently, a tent that looked like a booth at the April Fair costs the same as the gazebo). On top of that, we were the first to use the tent, so it didn''t have any decorations of any kind, just four bare flower pots.\nI have to say that both the cocktail party and the menu were very good, as was the terrace, the gardens, and the nightclub, but the food was horrible and, on top of that, at an unbelievable price. They told us that to alleviate what had happened, they would offer some small gifts to the bride and groom, and we''re still waiting for them. The only gesture was to politely say \"hello and goodbye\" to everyone, and of course, immediately charge over 1,000 euros for an extra hour of open bar and disco at the end. (At my daughter''s wedding elsewhere, they gave us that gift; that would have been a small gift they could have offered us, but they charged us every cent.)\nIn short, the treatment we received from Visi and Ver√≥nica was extremely unprofessional and unpleasant, lying the entire time and passing the buck. The only ones who have paid for this misfortune were the bride and groom that day and the future bride and groom who get married there. The company will collect their insurance and will have no problem rebuilding the gazebo in the future, but everything bad about the fire affects the bride and groom. They wash their hands of it perfectly.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Felipe Santorio Ramos","rating":1,"text":"CONTINUED COMPLAINT REGARDING THE PLASTIC TENT AT THE WEDDING:\n\nI don''t know where you got the idea that someone in our family told you in writing that we were absolutely delighted with everything that happened, because it''s simply not true. We tried, for the sake of the bride and groom, to make sure everything went smoothly and that people didn''t notice, or didn''t want to notice, that the tent where the reception was held was awful. And the truth is, our friends and family made it a wonderful day, thanks to everyone. But, of course, we can''t forget that we were treated terribly when it came to providing us with a better-equipped and more attractive venue for the day. Therefore, we don''t think it''s fair that only the bride and groom should bear the brunt of the problem and the misfortune that occurred, as it has all had repercussions for them. You will, of course, collect your insurance, and you should have charged us for the tent venue at the price for a plastic tent, not at the price for a glass pavilion, because there''s no comparison between the two. And we''re still waiting for the compensation they were supposed to offer the couple, which never materialized. Furthermore, we''re not creating any insecurity for future couples getting married there; we''re simply telling the truth about what happened to us and how they took advantage of the excitement and, above all, the fear of a young couple terrified by what had transpired, nothing more and nothing less. And to make matters worse, when we went to collect the leftover wedding items, they treated the people who came very badly and rudely, which was highly unprofessional of them.","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"Marcos Ramirez","rating":5,"text":"A beautiful venue for events, the staff are very attentive and provide personalized service, and the scenery is stunning. It''s a perfect location for all types of events, regardless of the date.","time":"2 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
