 Meli√° Hotel</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN3Kudm7bjDKhvxyrIyiByyibIddoNN9oR84uqwxQfNYqDaWjTVPKB2AjFd5aBh6l1Qw1GLFxpqjXQffP6hLNEpdOR_goia01YhdDF13XN39YAZeP0fN9mNUV-xTi5yjZ4VmXo7M9kKpM7G8HTNWIEzOmt9bWAXDJKvi-Ow8TZ31xL3i0iFpjxkjEnMHfWmhhuf-oOsF4_-IC2UIxwulHyYVJ0PoGULzIPm7AHTOfdOXP4cMyKUTW29aDxxmN7XscSejTniozqiU8EcXz15cWJ4ByeBdahPgR3Eieii9dR1LiQ","width":800,"height":533,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/115729704678949234658\">Palacio de los Duques Gran Meli√° Hotel</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN2rgPWd7RTwUytcxxx8G51gBx--6YfQ6VVTpN51dTq1aKI6SrLx1m_RrIsDtFDlzTxK0tcRChWC8MsZuRJuW8kki8l-DfWBEMzlRPjM10jZ3NsTL7O62A10e6FaDpKxhEcU18jBi1zlc8grjUgD91T6Gr7WIylz8jhhH0QKbJgVCr1RBItuFe3tWvbMGHsOMvPWY_L5l3N_xNkFRGbGTv7lFsdeSslXkjs4Dh4gk0IBQwHyQ8pNbONkBlIxOYN0OOLw3Qo8XCSYJg81lYOJUlHQv0xbTWtXQNjO0OJbRLg6pQ","width":2000,"height":1501,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/115729704678949234658\">Palacio de los Duques Gran Meli√° Hotel</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Pilar Albertson","rating":5,"text":"My partner and I just spent five days at the Melia Palacio de los Duques .....it was possibly one of the best holidays we have experienced.  The hotel was in a fantastic location, on a quiet street simply a block away from the Gran Via shopping area.  We didn''t come to shop....we simply wanted a place where we had some quiet time away from the hustle and bustle of the crowds.  When we arrived, we were greeted with the greatest of respect and gratitude.  We were given a lovely tour of our room and welcomed to the Melia hotel.  The room was quiet and serene, absolutely beautiful and tastefully decorated.  We had a beautiful bath tub in the room surrounded by glass, but it still afforded privacy if one needed that.\nWe experienced a wonderful buffet breakfast each morning, and the selection was abundant.  Over the holiday season the hotel had incredible entertainment of a guitar singer for breakfast and choir chorus singing carols at night\nBut more than anything, there were gifts of kindness and the staff always went above and beyond to afford a private but luxurious stay.  Thank you to everyone who made our stay so absolutely magical.  We hope to be back, but if not, the memories of this holiday and the welcoming atmosphere of this beautiful hotel  will stay with us for a very long time.","time":"a week ago"},{"author":"lenswork4","rating":5,"text":"From check in to check out, this hotel is outstanding in every way! Staff are helpful and attentive at every turn. Our room was spacious and well-appointed with everything a guest might need from an excellent bed for sleeping to a desk and chair for writing or catching up on work. Bathroom contained upscale toiletries and plenty of them. Lots of outlets to plug in your electronic devices for sure or charging, and they are located at convenient spots around the room. Room was also very quiet with no noise from street or hallway, making it easy to sleep and relax. Location is close to some major cultural attractions including the Teatro Real, Royal Palace, Puerta del Sol, and Plaza Mayor. I highly recommend the ‚Äúred level‚Äù experience because the lounge that includes breakfast, snacks, and drinks is a buffet of tasty delights and drinks to satisfy your cravings. I will stay here during my next visit to Madrid.","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Chandima N Dayantha","rating":5,"text":"The location is great, walking distance to palace and other highlights.\nHotel staff was friendly, courteous- service was excellent (ie. Ritz-Carlton level).. From concierge to resturant staff to attendants/vallet, They went out of their way to adress every need. They even helped us with locating our lost baggage working with airport authorities since we werent fluent in Spanish and while we were out sight seeing. The club level \"red\" we had really came with open bar and special quiet areas for dining and was really worth it. Rooms were excellent even came with hair iron, steam iron and welcome fruit bowl etc. Attention to detail was amazing -even provided plugs that were compatible to American electrical items. These were truly appreciated since we didn''t have our checked baggage. Their free car service was also a pleasant surprise with English speaking drivers and limo type seating.\n\nRoof top had great views sunset or morning. Gym was well equipped.\n\nBut really the service of the staff puts this hotel at 6stars, unfortunately only 5stars available.","time":"3 weeks ago"},{"author":"B Lee","rating":5,"text":"We had a wonderful experience.  The staff is professional, friendly, and helpful.  We ate breakfast buffet and dinner twice at the hotel.    The food is fresh and delicious. I especially liked the breads that they bake daily, so delicious. The hotel was beautifully decorated for the Christmas Holiday.","time":"a week ago"},{"author":"Elana P","rating":5,"text":"We greatly enjoyed our stay at the Palacio de los Duques Gran Meli√° Hotel. From the moment we arrived, we were treated with kindness and warmth from the hotel staff. The hotel is in a quieter area which was nice, but still very walkable to the main attractions. The hotel itself is beautiful and the room was comfortable. We really enjoyed the breakfast, it was delicious! Paula at the concierge was amazing and gave us a map of tapas restaurants to check out.\n\nWe would happily return next time we visit Madrid and highly recommend!","time":"a month ago"}]'::jsonb,
