 and advice on the time spent there.\n\nI want to to return just for a retreat and take full advantage of the pool and surrounding nature.","time":"a year ago"},{"author":"Anouchka DeLange","rating":5,"text":"Fabulous stay. Anita and Miguel are wonderful hosts. After a long trip we enjoyed the pool and it''s incredible views. They served us a delicious diner in the very unique garden terrace. So peaceful.\nOur room was beautifully decorated, very clean and once again the views were amazing.\nThis place was magical, we''ll certainly be back and if you are thinking about going then just go, it is really incredible, run by a wonderful family.","time":"a year ago"},{"author":"Chris Braithwaite","rating":4,"text":"Lovely rural location just outside of town and wonderful host in Anita . Rooms very comfortable indeed .","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Gemma Wills","rating":5,"text":"Had such a lovely night here - a late arrival in the rain and the host Anita waited up for us and cooked a splendid meal and wine. A restful night sleep in a cosy cave like room with all the little things you need like conditioner and hair dryer and soft bath towels. Super friendly with our two dogs and great for walking them in the morning on their huge plot of land. Will definitely be back - thank you ü©∑","time":"a year ago"}]'::jsonb,
