ating":5,"text":"Fantastic luxury hotel and super comfy bed. Chambermaid service slightly erratic as sometimes would return to find no cups in our room or a hotel dressing gown had disappeared but all rapidly resolved with a quick phone call! Fantastic central location and super friendly and helpful staff.","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"Aaron Matto","rating":5,"text":"Such a fantastic hotel and staff. Incredible experience start to finish. Everyone was super nice and helpful. We even accidentally left behind some clothes and they found a way to get it to us at our next town in France. Highly recommend this hotel!!","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"Familia BB","rating":3,"text":"We stayed here on 16th July for one night at the last minute. My brother made the booking as he is a frequent Marriott customer and had some way of doing so - when I had looked there was no room.\nOur stay was very pleasant. Our children were not put in an adjacent or interconnecting room as asked for and we were not able to receive an upgrade because it was a last minute booking - understood.\nThe frustrating part started at our check out. I paid the bill assuming that all was being charged. There was no breakdown of charges at all - just the final amount. I asked for the invoice to be sent to my email address but it has never arrived.\nThe hotel had charged 200‚Ç¨ extra on my card for expenses during our trip which I expected to be returned. Later they charged 29,95‚Ç¨ and a further 229,95‚Ç¨ on the card. We had invited a friend for breakfast so I presumed the 29,95‚Ç¨ was an extra breakfast charge.\nA few days later, nothing had been returned, so I called reception to enquire. Everyone was too busy, could I call later? I called again the next day. No one was available. They asked me to write an email. I wrote an email. No answer nor confirmation of the receipt of the email. I called again. The third time. Could someone please respond to me? I was told that they would. A few days passed. Yesterday I resent the email and added a few words about how frustrated I was that no one had deemed my query important enough to respond. I received a quick email informing me that breakfast wasn‚Äôt included and that I had been charged extra for them.\nWhy not prevent all of this wasted time and misunderstandings by showing me a detailed bill on checking out? I had to call 3 times and send two email for this very simple point to be clarified. What a waste of time and bitter end to what was a nice albeit expensive stay.","time":"4 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
